            <b>Dining :</b><br />
            <img border="0" height="1" hspace="0" src="http://www.kerala-tourism.net/gifs1/bdline.gif"
                vspace="2" width="243" /><br />
            The Restaurant &amp; Bars at the Le Meridien include the vibrant Treasure Trove,
            specializing in Mexican, Indian, Lebanese, Thai and local cuisine; a specialty restaurant
            featuring Oriental cuisine and seafood delicacies; Jules Bar, at the lobby level,
            the perfect place to unwind and listen to music while enjoying a drink or a cigar;
            Library Lounge, off the lobby, offers a 24-hour menu and selection of reading material.<br />
            <br />
            <br />
            <b>Conference and Banquet facilities :</b><br />
            <img border="0" height="1" hspace="0" src="http://www.kerala-tourism.net/gifs1/bdline.gif"
                vspace="2" width="243" /><br />
            A fascinating Kerala thatched roof in the best of local traditions, a sprawling
            riverside lawn as far as the eye can see, the stirring ripple of an oar wading through
            the backwaters, inspiration, strikes in myriad ways at the truly extraordinary International
            Convention Center at Le Meridien Cochin-Kochi. The center offers world-class convention
            facilities that are unmatched in the country and is an ideal venue for meetings,
            conferences &amp; seminars for the corporate world.<br />
            <br />
        The conference and Banquets
            center features a total of 9 spacious Conference Halls ranging from 2,700-14,000
            sq. ft, accommodation capacity of 500 to 2000 people, an exclusive lobby sporting
            a traditional Kerala wooden roof, a total of 52,000 sq. ft. of air-conditioned area,
            an impressive 8,000 sq. ft. riverside lawn and ultra-modern conferencing facilities,
            ISDN Internet access, audio visual conferencing and video projection facilities.<br />
            <br />
            For smaller meetings and seminars, guests can avail of the private meeting rooms,
            which, while providing an intimate atmosphere, can accommodate up to 8 to 10 guests.<br />
            <br />
            <br />
            <b>Recreation :</b><br />
            <img border="0" height="1" hspace="0" src="http://www.kerala-tourism.net/gifs1/bdline.gif"
                vspace="2" width="243" /><br />
            Exclusive recreational facilities are available at the hotel. Experience the revitalizing
            properties of an Ayurvedic massage and treatment at the Yoga Center. The Gymnasium
            at the top floor overlooking the backwaters gives an added impetus to the experience
            of rejuvenation. Relax in the sauna and steam room. There is also an outdoor swimming
            pool with a separate whirlpool, tennis court and a wide range of facilities for
            children, water sports/boating fishing facilities.<br />
